        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 10:27PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 1027 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 16 miles north of Hays, or 22 miles north of Zortman,
moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hays, Fort Belknap, and Lodge Pole.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
